    "en": "For patients at very high risk who do not achieve their goal on a maximum tolerated dose of statin and ezetimibe, combination with a PCSK9 inhibitor is recommended.\nVery high risk is defined as:\n1.Stroke plus another major atherosclerotic cardiovascular disease (coronary artery disease, carotid artery stenosis, peripheral artery disease, or atherosclerotic renal artery stenosis) or\n2.Stroke plus multiple high-risk conditions (hypertension, diabetes, dyslipidaemia, thromboembolic disease or risk factors).",
